storyInfo: Harmonie comes across someone that knows about her past, and who proposes extricating her from her intelligence work, but she does not accept.

attributes.content: Long time no see, Rosalie.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: Rosalie!
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: —Ah, darling Rita.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: It's been an awful while since we last got to chat, hasn't it? Such a shame we couldn't be in the same accommodation like we were before.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Really, Royal Guard runs far more arduous militarization drills than either of us could've imagined, wouldn't you say?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Did you make it to the entrance exams on the day?
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: *cough* *cough*... What has you asking that? Of course I made it—I wouldn't be here otherwise.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: No, nothing... Here, your Introduction to Military Science. The notes you left in there were very helpful, much appreciated.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: I was going to give it back the morning of the exam, but I left before I saw you. It's been sitting in the back of my mind.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: Want to get dinner together? We can catch up on the way. You can pick a dress for me to wear on my off day.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: Sadly not. I'm on my way to that ball Stefanie's hosting.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: You mean that Leithanian count's daughter?
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: I hear she's quite rich with contacts. Merchants wanting an inroad or musicians and playwrights in need of a referral can't go wrong in her social circle.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: The last time I ran across you, you were going to that army staff officer's granddaughter's soirée. Military families like that are always on the lookout for a few trustworthy aides to groom.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: Not that that should've had anything to do with your goals. You used to hate these noisy social events.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: Don't say that, Rita. Can't I just enjoy a little dance?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Fine.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: We'll chat the next time you're free, then.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: Don't look so crestfallen.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: We need a little time to find our own rhythm in new environments, that's all, no?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: (Humming) Like the steps of a dance. Oh, what tough luck—I was so badly hoping you'd accompany me.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Rosalie, do you remember why we worked so hard to get into the Royal Guard Academy?
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: Well, there's a silly question. To become outstanding servicemen, of course.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Right. Not officers, not military aristocracy. Servicemen. I don't want to be the Skamandros whose own safety supersedes all, like my father.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: And you want to be the kind of serviceman who can staunchly uphold order, as our tutor did.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: What I'm saying is... if you're worried about anything, you can talk to me.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: I don't think we've visited our tutor's grave yet, not since she passed on.
attributes.name: Rita

attributes.content: Ah... Terribly, awfully sorry, but I'd better be going, Rita.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: So say the papers. The 'Londinium-Kazdel Association of Economic and Cultural Exchange.'
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Some duke, God knows who, threw masses of Sarkaz mercs into Londinium. Their own pieces in the game, so to speak.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Well, I quite disagree.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Oi, keep schtum. If you know inside details, then I'm the last person who wants to hear.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Oh, my. The duke most likely to control Victoria? The aristocracy's rumors of where the Lion King's heir has ended up? The cities that might be expecting riots soon...? Not even one bit curious?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: What good does knowing that stuff do for me? I don't even want to know which City Hall member's family tutor you are.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Were, I mean. Your tutor thing's probably past tense now.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: So it is. I just wrapped up the final course yesterday.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: The young master has a grasp of plenty enough knowledge by now. He won't be needing me anymore.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Haha... and I assume you have plenty enough intelligence from snooping around there.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Enough for my boss to take this assignment on himself, and add a few more decorations to his wall of honor, you mean?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Ahem, *cough* *cough*... I'm not going to talk about anyone behind their backs.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: *sigh* You ought to keep a few measures in place, to avoid anyone stealing your credit.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Well, these things do happen. What's the use in minding it?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Enough, now. I'll take a fashion magazine.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Coming up.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: From now on, anyone who's got a special coin like yours, no matter who, gets to buy this magazine, right? Just checking.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Don't worry, I've done all the liaison work. You won't possibly mess this up.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Besides, you know nothing of the situation. Even if someone comes knocking on your shutter, it's not like they can do anything to you.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: There'll be no waves in your peaceful life, and all that's coming will be the pay we promised you.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Heheh, guess you've read me to boot.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Thank God for this income. I can send my kids to a better school, and they can become proper gentlemen.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Oh, yeah, how long'd it take for you to cover up that serviceman's valor of yours? I can tell all the officers I know even out of uniform, but not you.
attributes.name: Newsagent

attributes.content: Serviceman?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: I am part of the military, yes, but I never once said I was ever a serviceman.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Well, toodle-oo, I have an invitation to a dinner party. I'd better be on my way.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: No matter if a city plate collapses one day, or the blood forms a river through the Palace of Westhaleg, I'll be out of it, carrying on with my life the same as it ever was.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: I've seen enough of all these clever-clogs exuding their dignity.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Right, then, let's have a look... What news has my fine informant brought me?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Here's a letter...
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: ...that's been changed out already? They've stuck a note inside.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: '...I know your identity, but I am not an enemy of Victoria.'
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Dearie, now, that single sentence certainly isn't going to show if your interest is in aiding me, or kidnapping me.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Everyone loves to say they do it 'for Victoria.'
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Whether you were hanging the Lion King or bracing the royal family together, you thought were defending Victoria all the same.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: If everyone's efforts were aligned, we wouldn't be in need of intel-sniffers like yours truly.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Perhaps I'll need to pass a message on at the party tonight. Have this mysterious figure's intentions cleared up once and for all.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Have you heard? Two of City Hall's holdouts are finally caving in. They're restoring a fleet of steam tanks, and issuing a decree to relax the restrictions on factory owners.
attributes.name: Curious Noble

attributes.content: Hahah! At least the money we've been spending on them hasn't gone to waste.
attributes.name: Pompous Merchant

attributes.content: The older they get, the more reluctant they are to take a stand. It's all normal fare to give the army more weapons, they're just scared people will ask: Whose army is this? Who are they fighting?
attributes.name: Pompous Merchant

attributes.content: Ever since we lost the Lion King, they've been harder and harder questions to answer.
attributes.name: Pompous Merchant

attributes.content: Oh, pooh to that. Do you remember that doddling Assembly Member, the one sickness took in her own bed last month?
attributes.name: Curious Noble

attributes.content: Her neighbor told me, everyone was hearing horrible screams muffled through the walls that night. Would you say illness wasn't the true culprit? I wouldn't dare.
attributes.name: Curious Noble

attributes.content: That's what the old guard get for not wanting to relinquish their powers.
attributes.name: Pompous Merchant

attributes.content: Come, let's poke our heads into the ballroom. Allow me to fetch you a glass of wine.
attributes.name: Pompous Merchant

attributes.content: Conspiracies, bribes, assassinations... oh, there's nothing new under the sun.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: It's about time I dropped by the balcony. I should have good company to meet there.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Good evening, Miss Harmonie.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: Dearie me...
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Do you have a moment?
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: Not particularly, no. If you aren't careful enough with what you say, my Arts will make waterworks in your windpipe and seize you by the throat.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: You react very fast.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: I do like your complexion. Your breathing isn't coming at a rush, either.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: You're misunderstanding me. That note I snuck into your intelligence network wasn't meant to intimidate you at all.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: Then carry on. What exactly is it you want from me?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: A marquess sent me to convey goodwill.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: If you're of a mind to assist with our work, you should at least have some valid intel on you, no?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: No. I'd like to offer you a new destination.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: You were coerced into becoming intelligence personnel, serving the shambling rot of the Lion King's army. It does disservice to your talents.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: You shouldn't let yourself be tormented by a little years-old blunder either, and that's not to mention how you were completely in the dark at the time. It simply isn't your fault.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: They did me plenty of favors in order to cover that scandal up.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Don't you think you know a little too much?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Miss, I'm baaack. Your letter's been delivered.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Tomorrow being the entrance exams and all, I'd like to consult you on a few more questions I have. Mainly about how they test Originium Arts...
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: ...Is nobody in?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Miss? Are you alright?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Familiar knocking sound, most likely the kind of saber Miss uses... *gasp* What if somebody's robbing her?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: A seasoned serviceman like her should have all the ease in the world ridding herself of a few bandits. Although, this is the perfect chance to test my own abilities a little.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: The smugglers are all down! Enter the warehouse and sweep!
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Voice

attributes.content: Miss... Miss Horley?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: There's still an accomplice in here!
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Voice

attributes.content: Weapons down! Hands up!
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Voice

attributes.content: Who are you lot?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Got the full situation out of her?
attributes.name: Stern Officer

attributes.content: We've finished questioning. She's a student of Horley's. Still quite young. She didn't know a single thing about this gang reselling military goods.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: She has acted as their middleman on multiple occasions by delivering Horley's letters, but she hadn't a clue what she was passing on, nor did she ever have suspicions about her teacher.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: Horley took up a teaching post at a noble's private secondary school after being discharged. No criminal record for the past five years, very esteemed by her students.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: As far as the one here recalls, Horley never showed signs of involving any students as her accomplices. We can likely go without inspecting the rest of the student body.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: We've been holding her for two days. I know it's only been a normal interrogation, no deliberate pressure, but judging by what details we've observed, she's 100% honest.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: Alright, let her in. We'll run this as planned.
attributes.name: Stern Officer

attributes.content: Do you now understand the full course of the incident?
attributes.name: Stern Officer

attributes.content: My tutor committed a serious crime, and I was an accessory to it under unwitting circumstances... That's more or less what I've gathered.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: If you don't mind my asking, how has Miss...?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: She refused to cooperate, going so far as to incite a violent clash with the military. The only option she gave us was death.
attributes.name: Stern Officer

attributes.content: As for the resale of military goods, we've been on that trail for over a year. Horley took advantage of her military connections to serve as a key figure in the resale chain. That cannot be denied.
attributes.name: Stern Officer

attributes.content: We would desire for you not to sympathize too greatly with her.
attributes.name: Stern Officer

attributes.content: Was she a good teacher?
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: She...
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: She was a firm, strong fighter. I very much admire the strength she displayed.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: The things I learned from her were worth more, I think, than what I ever picked up in my etiquette class or social speaking drills.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: The idea she'd been doing this, and then failed, and fell, in this manner...
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: ...It's somewhat beyond what I would've expected. That's all.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: I respected her. Nothing more than that.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: We express our acknowledgement of the shock this incident has been to you.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: Please be assured, we won't be investigating your conduct, nor will we regard you as her accomplice.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: However, we desire for you to be the sole civilian who knows of this. You must maintain silence on the facts of this incident.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: Horley, along with two other soldiers who participated in the resale, will be recorded as assistant military to this operation.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: Remember: they 'bravely gave their lives in the fight.' That is what you should say to your classmates, your professors or anyone else, once news of her death reaches your campus.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: In addition, they'll be posthumously awarded. We hope you'll understand that we've put much thought into upholding the reputation of the woman you respect after her death, which we desire to grant her some dignity in.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: Mm, I understand the matters on which I should be silent.
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: We're very glad we could reach a consensus. There'll be some favors done for you.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: Favors?
attributes.name: Rosalie

attributes.content: Your account was, you visited her to prepare for the Royal Guard Academy entrance exams.
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: You'd like to get into Royal Guard, correct?
attributes.name: Gentle Officer

attributes.content: I'm just one of the military insiders from back then, by coincidence.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: If you came here to reminisce with me, then you really are courteous to a fault.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: After all, that was however many years ago. Even I don't remember it all off the top of my head anymore.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: I sympathize with what you went through years ago—that's exactly it. I can't bear to see a youngster with such limitless prospects not get the credit she deserves.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: I imagine you've noticed, somewhere in there, that your life fell out of your control ever since that affair.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: Despite getting into Royal Guard, you were forced to change identities and go fully incognito without ever graduating, and when it comes to intelligence work, forging genuine interpersonal relationships is a tall order.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: Fortunately, you could consider yourself lucky all the same. The Marquess seems to take a very vested interest in your abilities. You can get in touch with him via my referral. Perhaps you could even strive to become a personal aide.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: You can free yourself from your identity as an intelligence agent, and obtain a higher status doing it.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: Is phrasing it that way able to win your confidence?
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: Yes... that's all it is, no more.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Could you elaborate?
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: Don't you mind, that was just a little private monologue.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: My opinion is, if we carry on like this, my staff and the skin of your throat may just threaten to close their own distance.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: But upon those words, Harmonie stows her staff away.
—You're invited to leave now.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Madam, if you're declining because the difficulty of disengaging from your intel work worries you, then please trust that we have methods sufficient to aid you.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: It seems you think I'm dictated to hate my life and my lot in it.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: You've made a—not uncommon misunderstanding, I'll say. Conspiracies bury themselves all throughout life. So many little incidents are secretly the grand designs of master architects like yourself, am I wrong?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: You'll have seen that sort of thing a great deal, as an intelligence worker.
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: Quite. I've gotten fairly sick of seeing it, and even fairly sick of doing it.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: The fact of the matter is, nobody forced me into intelligence work. Some professors selected me, I agreed, and that was that.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Do you know something? If I really, truly hadn't the power to control my own life, I'd be compelled to kill you here and now, so as to avoid you bringing any hassle to my door.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: But I very much take a liking to you.
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Now, we were here to take part in a dinner, weren't we?
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: Harmonie turns away with light grace.
Inside the hall, the ensemble bows and readies to begin performing. The bright fixtures shine through the floor to ceiling windows, outlining her in a glowing silhouette.
(Humming)
attributes.name: Harmonie

attributes.content: With carefreeness, she lifts her arms, and spins a full circle.
There in the courtyard, she dances on her own in brisk, spry steps.
Who... will you be having your dance with?
attributes.name: Kind-Faced Noble

attributes.content: The Feline named Harmonie gives no answer.
